# Data & backend (client-side)

KMP client data layer — not server schema (see `supabase-backend.mdc` for SQL/RLS).

## Repositories

- Implement `domain/repository/` and domain ports (`NutritionSessionCoordinator`).
- **Personal/local:** `NutritionRepositoryImpl` → `NutritionLocalStore`.
- **Household shared:** `OfflineFirstNutritionRepository` + `NutritionSyncEngine` (outbox on push failure) + Supabase Realtime.
- **Auth/household:** `SupabaseAuthRepository`, `SupabaseHouseholdRepository`, `SupabaseHouseholdCollaborationRepository`.
- Map DTOs ↔ domain at boundary; composables never see DTOs.

## Sync & offline

- Local-first reads from `NutritionLocalStore`; push via sync engine when online.
- Week key scopes grocery, meal plan, AI grocery per household week.
- Conflict strategy: server wins on pull; outbox retries on push failure.
- Test: `OfflineFirstNutritionRepositoryTest`, codec round-trips.

## Services

- Implement `domain/service/` in `data/service/` (e.g. `LocalNutritionAiAssistantService`).
- AI/business rules stay in **domain** (`NutritionAiPlanner`); services delegate after optional delay.
- Validate inputs; return `Result` with stable error types — screen models map to UI.

## Storage & codecs

- `NutritionStorageCodec` for serialization; unit test encode/decode round-trips.
- `multiplatform-settings` for preferences where appropriate.
- Platform storage `expect`/`actual` only when no shared store exists.

## Observability

- `data/observability/` — Crashlytics breadcrumbs (Android); no credentials in breadcrumbs.
- Log via Kermit; redact tokens and emails in production paths.

## Error handling

- Fail fast on invalid input at service boundary.
- No silent swallow of persistence errors on write paths.
- Screen models: `NutritionAiState.Error`, snackbars, or inline field errors — not thrown exceptions to UI.

## Testing

- Repository tests with in-memory fakes / test store.
- Supabase repos: mock HTTP or integration scripts; unit-test DTO mapping and error parsing.
- When adding repository methods, update **all** fakes (`commonTest`, `androidInstrumentedTest`).
